
Overview of noun spice

The noun spice has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) spice -- (aromatic substances of vegetable origin used as a preservative)
2. spice -- (any of a variety of pungent aromatic vegetable substances used for flavoring food)
3. spiciness, spice, spicery -- (the property of being seasoned with spice and so highly flavored)

Overview of verb spice

The verb spice has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) spice, spice up -- (make more interesting or flavorful; "Spice up the evening by inviting a belly dancer")
2. zest, spice, spice up -- (add herbs or spices to)
